      "question": "If the polynomial $p(x) = x^4 - 6x^3 + 16x^2 - 25x + 10$ is divided by another polynomial $g(x) = x^2 - 2x + k$, the remainder comes out to be $x + a$. Find the values of $k$ and $a$.",
      "answer": "$k = 5, a = -5$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Perform polynomial long division of $p(x)$ by $g(x)$.",
          "Equate the obtained remainder expression to $x + a$.",
          "Compare the coefficients of $x$ and the constant term to solve for $k$ and $a$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$x^4 - 6x^3 + 16x^2 - 25x + 10 = (x^2 - 2x + k)(x^2 - 4x + (8-k)) + (2k - 16 + 25)x + (10 - k(8-k)) \\\\ \\text{Remainder } R(x) = (9 - 2k)x + (10 - 8k + k^2) \\\\ \\text{Given } R(x) = x + a \\\\ 9 - 2k = 1 \\Rightarrow 2k = 8 \\Rightarrow k = 4 \\text{ (Correction: check division steps)} \\\\ \\text{Correct division:} \\\\ x^2(x^2 - 2x + k) = x^4 - 2x^3 + kx^2 \\\\ \\text{Subtracting: } -4x^3 + (16-k)x^2 - 25x + 10 \\\\ -4x(x^2 - 2x + k) = -4x^3 + 8x^2 - 4kx \\\\ \\text{Subtracting: } (8-k)x^2 + (4k-25)x + 10 \\\\ (8-k)(x^2 - 2x + k) = (8-k)x^2 - 2(8-k)x + k(8-k) \\\\ \\text{Remainder: } (4k - 25 + 16 - 2k)x + (10 - 8k + k^2) = (2k - 9)x + (k^2 - 8k + 10) \\\\ 2k - 9 = 1 \\Rightarrow 2k = 10 \\Rightarrow k = 5 \\\\ a = 5^2 - 8(5) + 10 = 25 - 40 + 10 = -5$"
      },
